# 📘 Ladox HMRC MockSuite Documentation

Welcome to the **Ladox HMRC MockSuite v5 Developer Wiki** — the internal documentation hub for the mock implementation of the UK HMRC “Making Tax Digital (MTD)” 2026 compliance system.

---

## 🧭 What’s Inside

| File | Description |
|------|--------------|
| [Ladox_HMRC_MockSuite_v5_Full.md](./Ladox_HMRC_MockSuite_v5_Full.md) | Full internal developer guide |
| [README_summary.md](./README_summary.md) | Quick setup and reference |
| [changelog.txt](./changelog.txt) | Version history and audit trail |
| [/postman/](./postman/) | Postman + Newman test collections |
| [/assets/](./assets/) | Brand assets and visual materials |

---

## 🧰 How to Use

1. **Read the full documentation** in  
   [📘 Ladox_HMRC_MockSuite_v5_Full.md](./Ladox_HMRC_MockSuite_v5_Full.md)
2. **Set up your environment** using Node.js v20+ and npm.
3. **Run tests** via Postman or bash curl commands.
4. **Check metrics and audit logs** in `/logs/`.
5. **Integrate the OCR-based front end** (Ladox UI) for end-to-end testing.

---

## 🧪 Postman & Newman Testing
All automated test flows are stored in [`/docs/postman/`](./postman/).  
You can run them locally or as part of CI/CD:

```bash
newman run docs/postman/Ladox_MockSuite.postman_collection.json \
  -e docs/postman/env/local.postman_environment.json \
  --reporters cli,html,json
Reports will appear in /docs/results/ by default.

